SIMPLE: woman
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Woman
<hw>Wom"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Women</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>woman</ets>,
<ets>womman</ets>, <ets>wumman</ets>, <ets>wimman</ets>,
<ets>wifmon</ets>, AS. <ets>w⟦imac⟧fmann</ets>, <ets>w⟦imac⟧mmann</ets>;
<ets>w⟦imac⟧f</ets> woman, wife + <ets>mann</ets> a man. See
<er>Wife</er>, and <er>Man</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>An adult female person; a grown-up female person, as
distinguished from a man or a child; sometimes, any female
person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Women</qex> are soft, mild pitiful, and flexible.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And the rib, which the Lord God had taken from man, made he a
<qex>woman</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. ii. 22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have observed among all nations that the <qex>women</qex>
ornament themselves more than the men; that, wherever found, they are
the same kind, civil, obliging, humane, tender beings, inclined to be
gay and cheerful, timorous and modest.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Ledyard.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The female part of the human race;
womankind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Man is destined to be a prey to <qex>woman</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A female attendant or servant.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ By her
<xex>woman</xex> I sent your message.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Woman hater</b></col>, <cd>one who hates women; one who
has an aversion to the female sex; a misogynist.</cd>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj> </cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woman</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Woman
<hw>Wom"an</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To act the part of a
woman in; -- with indefinite <xex>it</xex>.</def>
<rj><au>Daniel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To make effeminate or womanish.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To furnish with, or unite to, a woman.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧To have him see me <xex>woman'd</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Womanhede</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Womanhead</ent>⟦br⟧
